A minimal extension would replace the following method

```js
    _onPurposeHintsChanged(method) {
        const purpose = method.content_purpose;
        this._purpose = purpose;
        this.emit('purpose-changed', purpose);
    }
```

with something like

```js
    _onPurposeHintsChanged(method) {
        const purpose = method.content_purpose;
        this._purpose = purpose === Clutter.InputContentPurpose.NORMAL
            ? Clutter.InputContentPurpose.TERMINAL
            : purpose;
        this.emit('purpose-changed', this._purpose);
    }
```

Minimal extensions like this are very unlikely to break on updates, so are generally very low-maintenance.

